result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Sentencing Hearing - April 15, 2014 - Original Transcript housed in 2013CF000111

13CF111 & 14CF10 cases called @ 1:31 p.m. Defendant Brian P Murphy in court with attorney Mark D Skvara.  Defendant Brian P Murphy in custody.  Scott C Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Upon motion of the State the Court dismisses and reads in 14CF10. PSI received by all parties and find no corrections or clarifications. The parties stipulate to 71 days CFTS. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Attorney Skvara. Statement by the defendant. 
Court orders: 66 month year term imprisonment - 2 1/2 yrs IC/3 yrs ES - 71 days CFTS. ES conditions: AODA, Abs Sob, Not be on the premises of any bars, Obtain HSED, Any terms or conditions deemed appropriate by supervising agent, $3000 fine plus the DNA surcharge and the blood draw cost w/ 60 DTP or PP, 36 mos DL rev/36 mos IID. Defendant is not eligible for CIP. Defendant is eligible for ERP. Bond previously posted to be applied. Appeal rights given.  Court orders the fine shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement.
Status conference on April 15, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant to maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant is prohibited from going on the premises of any bars.  No operation of any motor vehicles whatsoever.

13CF111 & 14CF10 Case called @ 3:00 p.m. Defendant Brian P Murphy in court with attorney Mark D. Skvara.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Skvara was intending to enter a plea on 13CF111 and will then proceed with possible resolution in 14CF10 at a later date. 14CF10 -  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. The court entertains waiver of the preliminary hearing. The court accepts voluntary waiver of the preliminary hearing. Defendant bound over for trial. Information filed by ADA Anderson. Receipt admitted - Reading waived. NG plea entered. Court orders $5000 Sig Bond w/ conditions. STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.

13CF111 - Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - Dismissed outright. Ct 3 - DRI. 13TR1638, 13TR1639, 13TR1640 & 13TR1641 - DRI. The court revokes the defendant's bond and orders a PSI. Bond forfeiture hearing to track along with these matters.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for April 15, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
